비고
2
컨텐츠 금지 규정
콘텐츠 정책
용어 범용화
2.1
귀하는 다음에 해당하는 컨텐츠를 (대화하기, 가르치기 등 게시 기능을 통해) 서비스에 게시할 수 없습니다.
귀하는 다음에 해당하는 콘텐츠를 서비스에 게시할 수 없습니다. 대화, 가르치기, 이름, 속성 등 여러분이 서비스 내에서 생성하는 텍스트와 다른 매체를 이용한 표현은 콘텐츠이며 콘텐츠 생성은 곧 게시로 간주합니다.
"콘텐츠"와 "게시"의 개념을 구체적이고 명확하게 정의
2.2
이 금지 규정을 위반한 컨텐츠는 서비스 내에서 신고 삭제 규칙에 의해 기계적으로 삭제될 수 있습니다. 저희에게 별도로 신고되는 경우, 해당 컨텐츠는 저희 내부 검토를 통해 삭제 여부가 결정됩니다.
이 정책을 위반한 컨텐츠는 서비스 내에서 신고 등으로 인한 삭제 규칙에 의해 기계적으로 삭제 또는 차단될 수 있습니다. 위반 수준에 따라서는 당신의 서비스 이용이 제한 될 수 있습니다.
정책 위반에 대한 조치 명확화
3.1
귀하는 서비스에 게시하거나 이와 관련하여 게시하는 IP 콘텐츠를 사용할 수 있는 비독점, 양도성, 재면허 가능, 로열티 무료, 전 세계 라이선스(이하 "IP 라이선스"라 함)를 저희에게 부여합니다. 즉,귀하가 심심이에 콘텐츠를 게시하는 경우, 해당 콘텐츠는 심심이 서비스에 노출될 수 있고, 이에 필요한 범위 내에서 사용, 저장, 복제, 수정, 공중송신, 전시, 배포 등의 방식으로 이용할 수 있도록 사용을 허락하는 전 세계적인 라이선스를 제공하게 됩니다.
귀하는 귀하가 서비스에 게시한, 그리고 그와 관련된 IP 콘텐츠를 사용할 수 있는 비독점, 양도성, 재면허 가능, 로열티 무료, 전 세계 라이선스(이하 "IP 라이선스"라 함)를 저희에게 부여합니다. 즉, 귀하가 심심이에 콘텐츠를 게시하는 경우, 해당 콘텐츠는 심심이 서비스에 노출될 수 있고, 필요한 범위 내에서 사용, 저장, 복제, 수정, 공중송신, 전시, 배포 등의 방식으로 이용할 수 있도록 사용을 허락하는 전 세계적인 라이선스를 제공하게 됩니다.
명확화
3.2
저희는 컨텐츠 금지 규정(섹션 2), 서비스 규칙, 운영 정책 및 관계 법령에 따라 언제든지 귀하가 생성한 컨텐츠를 삭제하거나 귀하의 서비스 이용을 제한할 수 있습니다.
저희는 콘텐츠 정책(섹션 2), 서비스 규칙, 운영 정책 및 관계 법령에 따라 언제든지 귀하가 게시한 콘텐츠를 삭제하거나 귀하의 서비스 이용을 제한할 수 있습니다.
SimSimi Policy on Rights and Responsibilities
These rights and responsibilities policies are the terms of service("Statement," "Terms," or "SRR") that govern our relationship with users and non-users of the SimSimi Service("SimSimi", "Service" or "SimSimi Service"). By using the SimSimi Service and accessing the SimSimi Service, you agree to this policy.
1. Age Restriction
You will not use SimSimi if you are under 13.
2. Content Regulation
2.1. You may not post any of the following content to SimSimi(through the publishing functions, such as talking and teaching).
2.1.1. Content that depicts explicit sex acts.
2.1.2. Content that depicts or encourages excessive violence or other dangerous conduct.
2.1.3. Content that includes or encourages threats, harassment, or bullying.
2.1.4. Content that includes or encourages sexual abuse of children.
2.1.5. Content that promotes hatred of a particular group based on  race, ethnicity, color, national origin, religion, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, family status, disability, medical or genetic condition.
2.1.6. Content that is improperly depicted in a natural disaster, cruel act, physical conflict, death, or other tragedy.
2.1.7. Content promoting illegal activities.
2.1.8. Content that infringes the intellectual property rights of others.
2.2. Content that violates these prohibitions may be removed mechanically within the Service by the removal rules. If reported separately to us, the content will be removed by our internal review.
3. User-Generated Content Management and Responsibility
3.1. You grant us a non-exclusive, transferable, re-licensable, royalty-free, worldwide license (the "IP License") to use the IP Content posted or related to the SimSimi Services. If you post any content on Services, the content may be exposed to SimSimi services, and you will be deemed to have granted to SimSimi and its partners a worldwide and permanent license to use, store, copy, modify, publicly transmit, display and distribute such content within the required extent.
3.2. We may remove content created by you or restrict your use of the Service at any time in accordance with our Content Regulation(Section 2), Service Rules, Operational Policies and applicable laws. Serious or repeated violations of any nature may result in the permanent block of your access permission to the Service.
3.3. You are solely responsible for the content you create. Please keep in mind that your device ID and activity records and materials within the Service may be submitted to law enforcement agencies in accordance with relevant laws and regulations.
3.4. Your content may be screened at any time by us or other users before posting, and passing the screening before publication does not guarantee that your content is in compliance with the content regulations.
4. Amendments
4.1. We’ll notify you before we make changes to these terms and give you the opportunity to review and comment on the revised terms before continuing to use our Services.
4.2. If we make changes to policies, guidelines or other terms referenced in or incorporated by this Statement, we may provide notice on the site governance page.
4.4. Your continued use of the SimSimi Services, following notice of the changes to our terms, policies or guidelines, constitutes your acceptance of our amended terms, policies or guidelines.
5. Disputes
5.1. You will resolve any claim, cause of action or dispute (claim) you have with us arising out of or relating to this Statement or SimSimi exclusively in Seoul Central District Court., and you agree to submit to the personal jurisdiction of such courts for the purpose of litigating all such claims. The laws of Republic of Korea will govern this Statement, as well as any claim that might arise between you and us, without regard to conflict of law provisions.
5.2. If anyone brings a claim against us related to your actions, content or information on SimSimi, you will indemnify and hold us harmless from and against all damages, losses, and expenses of any kind (including reasonable legal fees and costs) related to such claim. Although we provide rules for user conduct, we do not control or direct users' actions on SimSimi and are not responsible for the content or information users transmit or share on SimSimi. We are not responsible for any offensive, inappropriate, obscene, unlawful or otherwise objectionable content or information you may encounter on SimSimi. We are not responsible for the conduct, whether online or offline, of any user of SimSimi.
5.3. WE TRY TO KEEP SIMSIMI UP, BUG-FREE, AND SAFE, BUT YOU USE IT AT YOUR OWN RISK. WE ARE PROVIDING SIMSIMI AS IS WITHOUT ANY EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTIES INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT GUARANTEE THAT SIMSIMI WILL ALWAYS BE SAFE, SECURE OR ERROR-FREE OR THAT SIMSIMI WILL ALWAYS FUNCTION WITHOUT DISRUPTIONS, DELAYS OR IMPERFECTIONS. SIMSIMI IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ACTIONS, CONTENT, INFORMATION, OR DATA OF THIRD PARTIES, AND YOU RELEASE US, OUR DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, EMPLOYEES, AND AGENTS FROM ANY CLAIMS AND DAMAGES, KNOWN AND UNKNOWN, ARISING OUT OF OR IN ANY WAY CONNECTED WITH ANY CLAIM YOU HAVE AGAINST ANY SUCH THIRD PARTIES. WE WILL NOT BE LIABLE TO YOU FOR ANY LOST PROFITS OR OTHER CONSEQUENTIAL, SPECIAL, INDIRECT, OR INCIDENTAL DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS STATEMENT OR SIMSIMI, EVEN IF WE HAVE BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES. APPLICABLE LAW MAY NOT ALLOW THE LIMITATION OR EXCLUSION OF LIABILITY OR INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, SO THE ABOVE LIMITATION OR EXCLUSION MAY NOT APPLY TO YOU. IN SUCH CASES, SIMSIMI'S LIABILITY WILL BE LIMITED TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW.
6. Other
6.1. This Statement is an agreement between you and SimSimi, Inc. References to “us,” “we,” and “our” mean either SimSimi, Inc.
6.2. This Statement makes up the entire agreement between the parties regarding SimSimi, and supersedes any prior agreements.
6.3. If any portion of this Statement is found to be unenforceable, the remaining portion will remain in full force and effect.
6.4. If we fail to enforce any of this Statement, it will not be considered a waiver.
Any amendment to or waiver of this Statement must be made in writing and signed by us.
6.5. You will not transfer any of your rights or obligations under this Statement to anyone else without our consent.
6.6. All of our rights and obligations under this Statement are freely assignable by us in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, or by operation of law or otherwise.
6.7. Nothing in this Statement shall prevent us from complying with the law.
6.8. This Statement does not confer any third party beneficiary rights.
6.9. We reserve all rights not expressly granted to you.
6.10. You will comply with all applicable laws when using or accessing SimSimi.
